A sprawling vintage wooden workbench from the 1940s viewed from above, scattered with antique brass compasses, magnifying glasses, mechanical gears, rolled blueprints, and delicate clockwork mechanisms in various stages of assembly. Warm amber light streams through a dusty window, casting long shadows across worn leather tool rolls and glass jars filled with tiny brass screws. A half-assembled orrery sits in the center, its celestial rings catching the light. The scene evokes discovery and craftsmanship, with rich sepia tones and the patina of well-used instruments suggesting years of creative exploration and tinkering.
